I have never seen such a manga!!
Is this really 100 times better than KTM?
everyone puts their dishes in the bin on the table in front of the classroom.
Then 80 of the students go to play on the playground,
For example, Takahashi spends lunch break pretending to study.
So, if I covertly place my dishes on Takahashi's desk
while he disposes of his dishes...
Something this petty, a perfect crime?
It does not really live up to its title...
It is fine if he does petty things seriously.
Yeah, it is best to start out small.
But he just looked at me with a face that said I saw what you did
It was the first time my perfect crime...
Maybe all the perfect crimes I have committed so far...
Like finishing Yasuda's drill on my own,
or letting a sparrow loose in the classroom and disrupting class...
Maybe he is seen them all...
I suddenly became interested in Minami,
and I started observing him the following day.
When lunch ended, Minami did the same thing I did yesterday.
His was not a perfect crime, either.
Even after school ended, I kept following him.
To my surprise, Minami himself was following our classmate Kitamura!
I had done it with a random person before.
The next day, Minami tailed an upperclassman.
We kept this up every day for a week.
Then Minami came up to me.
I thought this was petty at first, but I am getting drawn in by the realistic art and how serious these guys are.
Because this is a kid's world, things like this are actually more realistic.
So that is how you will do it!
And so, the Perfect Crime Club was formed.
It is 100 times better than KTM!
I have never seen anything this good.
No, I can say it is an entirely new type of manga.
I can see the gutsiness and serious humor clearly in this one!
The ultimate form of Ashirogi Muto!
Save that for when we are serialized and go head to head with Niizuma...
But how did you think this up?
It is because we tried some of them out in real life.
I cannot tell you... you know?
If we told you, it would not be a perfect crime anymore.
And unlike the unconventional manga you have done before, this is not cynical!
Okay, we will go with this for the first chapter.
If you make any changes, keep them small.
Actually, messing around with it might make it worse.
I will jump right into our plans for chapter two, then...
A girl will join their group!
Right, that is a heroine-like name.
Mai is extremely calculating, and she loves mystery novels, so her deductive reasoning is excellent.
The current two members of the perfect crime club decide that they must have her abilities,
How will they get her to join?
It should be in a perfect crime-like way, right?
They will arrange a mysterious surprise for Mai's birthday,
which will lead her to investigate and eventually deduce their identities.
The serious humor can come from the usually unflappable Mai getting flustered,
and it will show her cuteness as a heroine!
I think it will be interesting that they let themselves be discovered.
You have already got it all planned out, huh?
Then you two should go ahead and make the second chapter.
It sounds like I am better off waiting to read it than hearing about it now.
What is going on with Ashirogi?!
There is not even a week left until the deadline for the storyboard!
Well, they will definitely make it in time, so let us stay calm
Okay, I will come right over.
It looks like Takahama finished his storyboard, so I will be heading out.
Should not Ashirogi be more important than Takahama right now?
I fixed everything like you said!
It is way better than last time!
I will not submit this to the serialization committee.
If it is good, then please submit it!
if Ashirogi does not submit a work that is as good as Niiuzma's to the next committee,
they will not be able to draw for Jack anymore.
It was the condition for them being allowed to quit Tanto.
So in order to make things easier for Ashirogi, you are asking me to swallow my tears?
I would have told you to go forward with this.
But now, I do not think you should submit a work at this level.
Because Ashirogi's is far better than this.
I have not shown it to the higher ups yet,
but their storyboard is pretty much complete up through the third chapter.
I can assure you that there is no way theirs will fail and yours will pass.
If you still want to submit it, I will try talking to the higher ups...
I cannot stand the idea of losing without a fight.
Besides, you are the one who always says
If you can just get serialized, everything else will work out!
We both worked hard on this hoping to get it serialized.
I should not have said that.
Up until now, getting a serialization was all that mattered.
Now, I have finally realizing that there is more to it than that.
Niizuma, I have some good news for you.
And it is starting in April!
It is because it got more popular than CROW.
Unless they are as popular as CROW h and +NATURAL, they will not be able to draw for Jack anymore.
Akira, you would usually say Ashirogi will not lose to you next time!
They sure are in a tight spot.
Even if they get serialized, they will have to draw even with CROW h and +NATURAL.
They have got some tough acts to follow.
Maybe they should change the condition to just getting serialized.
Well, Ashirogi will get what they deserve.
No matter what kind of manga they submit, I do not think they can easily measure up with Niizuma!
I will negotiate with the Chief Editor to consider their work as a normal manga
and not hold it up to Niizuma as a standard at the committee!
This is no time to act cool!
This is not a question of you or Hattori taking the blame!
This is about an author's career here!
We editors are in a position to determine an author's life
If it is bad, they will get what they deserve.
I needed a change of pace.
You can use your bike, but do not get in an accident.
It will be no laughing matter if you break your arm.
I would not be so clumsy.
Well, having a hobby is not a bad thing.
Ashirogi's under a condition like that?!
And their manuscript was not considered at the last committee...
The next committee is all they have left!
If Ashirogi cannot draw for Jack anymore, it will definitely have an effect on Niizuma.
So they are that determined, huh...
I will leave the rest to you, then.
Hey, I have done all I can with KIYOSHI.
We have brought the delinquent tournament all the way to Y-1.
It is my third year of serialization, and the ranking always floats around 10th place.
And there have not been any anime offers.
And now, Ashirogi is trying to get a serialization that can match Niizuma's work.
What is happened to the Fukuda Team?!
The deadline is the day after tomorrow... is there really nothing left to change?
He asked to see the storyboard we are submitting to the committee.
And you said that was okay?
He might be our rival next week!
and it is already the deadline, so what is the harm in showing him?
More importantly, I want to hear his thoughts on it.
I am not going to submit anything to the committee this time.
You do not have to go that far.
It is way better than mine.
Now I am fired up and ready to make something better; something that will not lose to Ashirogi Muto!
I was about to submit my pitiful storyboard to the committee.
And I will catch up to you soon!
After seeing Takahama's reaction, I am even more confident in this.
And I want to try hard for his sake, too!
It is much more than okay!
This is the first Christmas since you have been married.
Do not worry, it is fine.
We will be stuck to each other once you leave.
Let us get ready to celebrate while we wait for results from the committee.
I think the storyboard will pass.
Miura told us that Hattori praised it, right?
This is what I was looking for, he said.
They will not meet until their dreams come true, right?
Well, we met at the hospital and your wedding.
I will definitely make our dreams come true with Perfect Crime Club,
and we will be together like you two are soon!
Well, Mashiro, you sure are talking big!
You drew Miho a picture for her birthday, right?
She said she wanted to do something for you, too.
It is obviously Ashirogi this time.
It is got a good review from the higher ups.
It is hard to admit, but it looks like a sure thing.
I did not think they would do it like that.
And they will definitely get the kids' vote.
But really, I never thought the three of them could come up with such a good manga.
Strictly speaking, it was not just the three of us.
Well, it has not been decided yet...
Right, it has not been decided.
This time, it is not just about whether it is good or not.
Up next is Ashirogi Muto's Perfect Crime Club.
If I may say, I do not think there is a better work than this.
Everyone present gave it a good mark, and there appear to be no problems.
Only Yoshida believes that it is good, but needs some changes.
They are trespassing on school grounds.
It would not be good if children imitate this.
If you go by that reasoning, then every manga where someone hits someone else is no good.
because the story and art are both strangely realistic,
it seems easy to imitate, or rather, it makes you want to imitate it.
That should be taken as a laudable aspect.
We should proceed with discretion, but it should not be a problem.
If there is no problem on that front, then I believe it is the best work we have here by far.
It looks like Ashirogi finally found their way.
and even though it is serious, I was blown away.
It reminds me of the secret base I made as a kid.
Because it is a secret club.
In that way, it really is a shounen manga.
In elementary school, I tailed a girl I really liked to find out where she lived.
If you did that now, you would be a stalker!
Although we are having fun with old stories,
let us pass Perfect Crime Club with a unanimous yes
but before we say yes or no to this manga,
we first must consider whether it can beat Niizuma's manga, CROW and +NATURAL.
about not letting them draw for Jack if they cannot win against CROW and +Natural?
If it is a question of winning or losing...
Perfect Crime Club will be serialized, will not it?
But this time, it is not a question of being good or bad.
It is about whether it can compete with CROW and +NATURAL.
Well, we knew it would not be easy.
Well, you know, there are magazines other than Jack.
I heard about it from Aoki.
I am sorry for making you worry.
But we will definitely be serialized in Jack.
Shujin, if we do not pass, you will not give up on manga, will you?
What are you talking about, Saiko?!
I am just saying, What if?
In that case, we will draw for some other magazine and surpass Eiji that way.
That would not be the best option, but there would not be any other choice.
We will not quit being manga authors.
Sorry, but I just wanted to confirm that.
Even if we do not sell, we will do it for the rest of our lives!
W-Well then, shall we begin discussion on whether Perfect Crime Club h can win against CROWh and +NATURAL?
Is not this sort of a strange topic to discuss?
I think it can beat them!
Aida, this comes from one of your team members, right?
To beat Niizuma would mean to beat an already popular manga.
They cannot beat him so easily.
We will not know if they do not try!
Is not that what you always say?
This is a discussion about whether or not they have the potential to beat him!
If you put it that way, then any manga would have a small potential of winning!
This is about whether or not they can beat him right now.
This is very good, and the fact that it does not overlap with other serializations works in its favor.
I believe it is off to a good start.
But a good start is not enough...
Not if they cannot beat him.
When you put it that way...
The committee is running long, surprisingly.
I thought they would finish early today.
Should not they be wrapping up soon?
I wish that were true, but if they do not pass...
And I am worried that Hattori, who said it was really good, has been looking depressed this whole time.
Niizuma and Ashirogi have different levels of experience.
If you are talking about experience, I think Ashirogi's struggles have made them stronger in that area.
It does not make sense to compare two completely different types of manga on experience level.
We cannot seem to come to a conclusion on if it will win or lose.
We will decide it by majority vote.
Are we really deciding this on a vote, Chief Editor?!
Because the situation is so complicated, I believe it will be difficult for them to win.
Aida, you vote for win, right?
Win and Lose are tied at 2.
Win and Lose are tied at 3.
You have yet to vote, Chief.
All that is left is to get news of the serialization!
Saiko, do you honestly think that Perfect Crime Club can win against CROW and +NATURAL?
TRAP tied with CROW h once.
I do not think it can win against CROW and +NATURAL.
Th-Then, with a majority vote of 3 for Win and 4 for Lose,
Ashirogi Muto's Perfect Crime Club will not be serialized...
Perfect Crime Club h is good.
